Package: nistwctscanR
Title: NIST Atomic Spectra Log-Cosine Spectral Scan (R reproduction)
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("NIST WCT scan", "contributors", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "noreply@example.com")
Description: An independent R computational reproduction of the canonical
    Python NIST Atomic Spectra log-cosine spectral-density scanner
    (scripts/nist_wct_log_spectral_scan_FIXED.py). Reads NIST line-list CSV
    exports, bins line positions in logarithmic wavenumber coordinates, fits a
    Poisson log-linear baseline plus a one-mode cosine/sine harmonic via IRLS,
    scans the deviance improvement over a wavenumber-winding grid, and runs a
    parametric Poisson bootstrap. This is a computational reproduction only; it
    is not an independent dataset, an independent scientific confirmation, nor
    endorsed/certified/validated by NIST. NIST is the data provider only.
